What is balayage, and why is it popular?

Balayage is a French hair coloring technique that involves hand-painting highlights onto the hair for a natural, sun-kissed effect. It has gained popularity for its seamless blending and low-maintenance upkeep, making it a favorite choice among women seeking a lived-in hair color look.
